RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 75. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 25, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5 ,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANITA GRIGIO broke sharp to lead soon after the start, travelled kindly up front running on the turn, was headed outside at the top of the lane and battled stubbornly down the entire stretch to hold safe at the finish. MISS BOBBIT was between runners in the tracking flight with three eighths left to run, took up the chase with two furlongs still to go, headed the pacesetting winner in upper stretch and dueled to the wire outside making little gain while on the wrong lead to the line. WAKE UP MAGGIE travelled in mid pack in this small field early on, was shuffled to last while inside entering the turn, angled three wide outside five sixteenths to the finish, began to find her best stride in the five path turning for home, passing tiring runners and finished up a non threatening third. J M R BOLD VISION broke slow at the start, then was hustled between runners to chase the loose frontrunner inside on the turn and finished up evenly to hold for a minor role at the wire. STORMY SUZIE settled near the rear with rivals on either side down the backstretch, made little impact throughout the turn and had nothing to offer in the drive to the finish line. CARLA'S HONOR was outside runners stalking four deep with a half mile remaining, offered a brief rally three wide midpoint on the turn and retreated between foes in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SONET'S NAME took control up front leaving the chute, was comfortable dictating the pace on the turn, opened up when asked in mid stretch and held well in the end for the victory. CHARLOTTE'S SILVER was off slow to trail the field in the early stages of the race, started a rail move midpoint on the turn, shifted out splitting horses three wide at the quarter marker, continued to rally five wide in upper stretch, angled in to the two path for the final eighth and closed well to be a solid second. STOLE THE RING tracked in the second flight on the rail down the backside, chased the winner on the fence through the turn and upper stretch to gamely finish up inside to the wire being a clear third. NATASHA'S BIZNIZ settled inside in midfield at the half, roused on the rail with three eighths remaining advancing up the fence and showed good late interest to pick up the pieces for a minor share at the wire. MAKES SENSE TO ME pressed the pace three wide at the half mile marker, was nudged to go after the frontrunning winner three furlongs from the finish and was outside in the five path through the lane to finish evenly in the end. NICOLE'S SONG was in the tracking flight three wide outside of rivals down the backside, coaxed three furlongs out in the two path on the turn, had no gain on the leaders and faded between runners at the quarter pole. CLIFF'S HEAD was stalking in midfield outside of horses at the half, was asked through the turn and could not find more to be involved down the stretch. ABSOLUTE JEWEL settled outside near the rear down the backside, was ridden midway on the turn, offered little acceleration and could not play a part through the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLAT OUT VIXEN was relaxed in the middle of the pack on the rail down the backside, circled three wide with three furlongs remaining, assumed command when the straightened out for the drive and was going away comfortably when crossing the wire. COURTINGCOURTNEY forced the issue on the rail entering the backside, was reined in nearing the five eighths marker, roused on the fence three furlongs from home and battled between in the four path to win the place duel in deep stretch. CHEEKY PINT trailed the field into the first turn saving ground, began to pick up the pace inside at the half, waited between runners with three furlongs from the prize, angled four wide to rally at the quarter pole and lost the battle down the lane for the place share late. FORESTERS PRINCESS led the field in the two path entering the first turn, opened up some on the pack with five eighths left to run, continued to improve on the lead under a drive at the quarter pole and was swallowed up by the field in mid stretch. AMI'S LINK threw her head at the break, travelled near the rear three wide into the first turn, was relegated to last down the back straight and could not improve her position though final three furlongs.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPRING HIGH broke a step slowly, switched outside rivals and made an early advance outside to maintain contact with the field but still racing off the leaders, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, rallied widest to take the lead seventy yards from home and drive clear. SMILES FOR DAVID was lightly bumped into a rival at the start, outsprinted early, shifted in leaving the backstretch, saved some ground near the inside early on the turn, angled out six wide past the quarter pole, rallied along with and inside the eventual winner but was no match for that one while second best. SPEED CHESS prompted the pace from outside, went two to three wide on the turn taking command coming past the quarter pole, was clear through upper stretch, collared nearing the seventy-yards marker and outkicked. GIVE ME THE BOOTS broke a step slowly, was coaxed forward inside, chased from in behind the leading pair inside foes in the second flight into the turn, moved out four wide leaving that bend looming a threat at the top of the stretch, drifted in a bit in the lane and flattened out. ASHLEE'S RING was just lightly bumped at the start, chased from between runners in the second flight about three wide into and on the turn, moved out five wide leaving that bend, lacked the needed late kick. SWEET BOMBOLINI broke a bit awkwardly, brought up the rear racing off the rail, moved in a bit in upper stretch and ran on. FRAC TALES bumped a rival lightly at the start, set a pressured pace racing inside, came up empty. DROWNINGNCHOCOLATE raced outside the second flight mid-pack into the turn, dropped back and faded.

(Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JMR PURE SENSATION settled mid-pack racing two to three wide, was between runners midway up the backstretch, switched outside foes leaving the turn coming five wide into upper stretch with aim on the leader, drifted in just the slightest bit in upper stretch but rallied to take the lead a sixteenth out and drive clear. NIKKI NOOTS attended the early pace from outside then took charge to force the issue from outside, moved clear turning into upper stretch, drifted out just a bit at that juncture, was outkicked by the winner but kept on and just saved place. GROOM LAKE was held up in behind runners in the early going racing a bit awkwardly in that position, settled down soon after to track the leaders mid-pack and inside foes, moved out three wide turning for home, was guided out a bit further at the eighth pole as the leader drifted out some, kept on while trying to collar that one for the place but missed. STRONGER TOGETHER was bumped at the break and a tad slow to gather, gained forward position outside the second group on the first turn, advanced to the flank of the leading pair three to four deep on the far turn and was ridden along from the five-sixteenths, steadied slightly when in tight near the furlong marker and altered outside the eventual winner at that juncture, ran on but needed more. I AM RESILIENT raced off the pace inside, came out in upper stretch, was not a threat. ROBITAILLE was in just a bit tight between runners at the start, steadied on heels soon after just prior to heading iinto the first turn, trailed the field and was never near enough to threaten. BAYTOWN ELVIS bumped a rival at the start, was coaxed forward to clear and angled to the rail entering the first turn setting the early pace, was soon overtaken and pressed from inside up the backstretch, steadily weakened. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF STRONGER TOGETHER AGAINST JMR PURE SENSATION ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH NO ACTION WAS TAKEN AND RESULTS TO STAND AS IS.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOO MUCH VINO broke out on the start to trail leaving the chute, put in an early four wide move around runners nearing the half, was outside taking command at the midway point on the turn, opened up on the field turning for home and increased the lead crossing the wire. FOREST MAIDEN had a good spot watching the contesting leaders at the four furlong marker, was ridden to go after the top pair nearing the quarter pole, shifted out to be four wide at the top of the lane and ran on well edging away for the place share at the finish. WAR'S END KISS broke out to begin, settled near the back of the pack with a half remaining, was on hold on the rail into the turn, found a seam on the fence two furlongs out, shot on through, shifted out to the three path between foes in the stretch and closed in for third money. THUNDERHEAVYRAIN travelled in mid pack between horses down the backstretch, found a seam four wide with rivals on either side two furlongs from the finish, was in the mix in upper stretch for a share and finished evenly getting a small role in the end. CELTIC REVIVAL set the pace down the back straight, put away an early outside foe at the seven sixteenths marker, braced for the challenge outside by the winner in midturn and yielded on the fence at the furlong marker. A GAL FOR T J trailed the field four furlongs from the finish, travelled three wide making little impression outside on the turn, angled out five wide at the top of the lane and passed tired runners in the stretch. GOLDEN TRAIN was pushed out at the break, kept the early leader honest just outside running in early backstretch, began to give way seven sixteenths remaining and weakened between foes at the quarter pole. MORE GELATO travelled in the middle of the pack three wide in the beginning, was scrubbed on five sixteenths from the line, made no gain and was a non factor down the lane.

SWEEPING PASSION had a good position on the rail watching the top two into the turn, waited for the right time to pounce inside at the quarter pole, made a gutsy stretch run at the furlong marker to bid for the lead only to come up short settling for a solid third placed finish. SANDY GRACE settled near the back of the pack with a half mile remaining, put in a middle move around foes running on the turn and was one paced in the stretch drive. MISS MOLLY LALOU tracked three wide in midfield going into the turn, loomed four wide when straightened out for the drive to the wire and stalled in the final eighth. BRIDGE TO NOWHERE had a poor start, broke inwards, head cocked trailing the field considerably in the early stages, was ridden to get into contention at the half and had nothing to offer in the stretch due to trying to overcome her bad break. PRINCESS DIDI travelled just off the rail midfield down the back straight, could not make any headway on the turn and was not involved for the stretch run.
